article.headline: Nebraska 77, Tennessee 62
article.story: LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- John Turek scored 21 points to lead Nebraska to a 77-62 win Saturday over Tennessee. The Cornhuskers took advantage of dismal Tennessee shooting in the first half, building a 22-point lead midway through the second period. Nebraska (6-1) went up 50-28 with 12:25 remaining on a Jason Dourisseau dunk that brought the basket standard down. After the delay, Tennessee (3-1) made a comeback that cut the Husker lead to 11. Tennessee never got closer, even with Turek on the bench having fouled out with 5:50 remaining. Nebraska's last field goal came with 3:45 remaining. But the Huskers hit 16 of 19 free throws down the stretch to seal the game, led by Nate Johnson's 10-for-10 shooting. The first half was an exercise in futility for the Volunteers, who went more than 15 minutes without a field goal. Tennessee made just two 3-pointers and a dunk with 10 seconds remaining in the half, hitting only three of 27 shots. Nebraska made 11 of its 30 shots and opened a 10 point lead on Wes Wilkinson's 3-pointer with 3:48 remaining in the first half. The Huskers' biggest margin was 16 on John Turek's layup with 37 seconds left in the half. But Brandon Crump converted a 3-point play to cut the halftime lead to 30-17. Johnson had 14 points for the Huskers, and Corey Simms added 12. Crump led Tennessee with 25 points, nine of them in the final three minutes.
